# **Simon Game - HTML Documentation**

## **1. Overview**
This document describes the structure and purpose of the HTML file (`index.html`) used in the Simon Game. The HTML file defines the user interface and links external stylesheets and scripts to create an interactive memory-based game.

---

## **2. File Structure**
- `index.html` - The main structure of the webpage.
- `styles.css` - The stylesheet for UI styling.
- `game.js` - The JavaScript file controlling the game logic.

---

## **3. HTML Structure**

### **3.1. Head Section**
```html
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>Simon</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Press+Start+2P" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
```
- Defines the document character set as UTF-8.
- Sets the title of the webpage.
- Links the external CSS file (`styles.css`).
- Includes a Google Font (`Press Start 2P`).

---

### **3.2. Body Section**
```html
<body>
  <h1 id="level-title">Press A Key to Start</h1>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div type="button" id="green" class="btn green"></div>
      <div type="button" id="red" class="btn red"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div type="button" id="yellow" class="btn yellow"></div>
      <div type="button" id="blue" class="btn blue"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.3.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
  <script src="game.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
</body>
```
- **Heading (`h1`)**: Displays the game status (e.g., "Press A Key to Start").
- **Game Board (`div.container`)**:
  - Contains four colored buttons (green, red, yellow, and blue) arranged in a grid.
  - Each button has a unique ID (`id="green"`, `id="red"`, etc.).
- **JavaScript Inclusions**:
  - Loads jQuery from a CDN.
  - Includes the game logic script (`game.js`).

---

## **4. Functionality Overview**
- The webpage initializes with a title prompting the user to start the game.
- Pressing any key begins the game sequence.
- Players interact with the colored buttons.
- The JavaScript file (`game.js`) handles user input, game logic, and animations.

---

## **5. Future Enhancements**
- Improve UI responsiveness for mobile devices.
- Add accessibility features for better usability.
- Enhance animations and transitions for a smoother experience.

---

### **This document provides a structured understanding of the `index.html` file in the Simon Game project.**

